JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng premier David Makhura says he wants to work with Operation Dudula and other civic groups concerned about illegal immigration. But he says reserving jobs for South Africans first is not feasible. READ: Operation Dudula accuses SAPS of being involved in criminal networks Makhura has weighed in on South Africa’s porous borders which he says need to be tightened while remaining sympathetic to the plight of refugees. “As Gauteng provincial government we want to work with all organised civil society," Makhura said. READ: Operation Dudula members, police clash in Orange Grove "We want to work with organised civil society like Operation Dudula. We want to work with them and work with the law enforcement agencies.” * eNCA's Govan Whittles reports.